      "side": 1,
      "message": "The SkConic::chopAt() function seems to run into significant FP precision issues, so the cap on this test is lower than the quad case. To verify, I reimplemented SkConic::chopAt() using doubles (and changed the error check -- projection -- to doubles as well) and was able to raise this exponent to the same as the quad case.",
      "revId": "0f9783f0fa908966323f895146c95798d17e297c",
