      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T21:43:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We actually don\u0027t have to chop in doubles. We could just evaluate at tmin, tmax, and (tmin + tmax)/2 in double precision. Then just find the height of the triangle.\n\nWere you also running wangs_formula_rational_cubic_reference_impl in double precision?",
      "parentUuid": "afe8fdf0_12b292de",
      "revId": "0f9783f0fa908966323f895146c95798d17e297c",
